&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Digital Program Developer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Digital Program Developer designs, builds, and configures digital care pathways using GetWell’s content management and workflow platforms (Contentful and Total.js). This role translates clinical requirements into patient-facing digital programs by configuring content delivery, conditional logic, alerts, and multi-step workflows. You are the hands-on builder who brings care pathways to life.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Workflow Configuration &amp;amp; Development (≈70%)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Care Program Build &amp;amp; Configuration&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Configure multi-step digital care programs in Total.js/Program Composer&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement conditional logic, branching scenarios, and decision trees&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define temporal sequencing (e.g., pre- and post-procedure timelines)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Configure alerts, escalation triggers, and severity levels&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set up patient eligibility, enrollment, and progression logic&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Configure multi-channel communications (SMS, email, secure messaging)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Integrate data feeds, reference dates, and enrollment criteria&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Content Management (Contentful)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and structure patient-facing content including:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Educational modules and daily check-ins&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Surveys, assessments, and PROMs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Automated messages with personalization variables&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Model structured content and reusable components&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage media assets (video, images, PDFs)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support multi-language content (English, Spanish, others as needed)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logic &amp;amp; Rules Configuration&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build scoring logic, formulas, and threshold-based alerts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Configure skip logic, validation rules, and required fields&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define completion criteria and program states&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Map data capture requirements and field specifications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Testing &amp;amp; Quality Assurance (≈30%)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Testing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and execute end-to-end test plans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Validate all logic paths, alerts, and edge cases&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Test delivery across channels and platforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Verify data capture, storage, and reporting accuracy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform regression testing following updates or changes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Documentation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain configuration and logic documentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create workflow diagrams and architecture maps&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document business rules and decision criteria&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support version control and change management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build troubleshooting and support guides&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical &amp;amp; Platform Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3–5 years experience configuring complex workflows or automation platforms&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;(e.g., BPM tools, CRM workflows, marketing automation platforms)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of conditional logic, decision trees, and multi-step orchestration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years experience with modern CMS platforms&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;(Headless CMS preferred: Contentful, Sanity, Strap

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Opportunity:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Get Well is seeking a highly skilled and visionary Principal Engineer - AI Engineering to drive the development and implementation of advanced AI solutions. This role focuses on the technical execution of AI projects, leveraging expertise in Large Language Models (LLMs), multimodal AI systems, and agentic systems to create innovative healthcare solutions. The Principal/Staff Engineer will work closely with AI engineering teams, product teams, and cross-functional stakeholders to deliver scalable, reliable, and impactful AI technologies. This role serves as a key interface between AI engineering teams and product teams, translating technological capabilities into tangible healthcare solutions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position reports directly to the VP, Product Development, working collaboratively across multiple teams to advance the organization&#39;s AI capabilities and strategic objectives.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;AI Solution Development&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, develop, and implement AI solutions leveraging unimodal and multimodal Large Language Models (LLMs) and agentic systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and integrate agentic systems using frameworks like CrewAI, LangChain, and LangGraph to enable autonomous decision-making and workflow automation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Incorporate emerging AI technologies into existing product ecosystems to enhance functionality and user experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute model training, fine-tuning, and optimization of inference engines for high-performance AI systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure technical excellence in AI solution design and implementation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate and integrate emerging AI technologies into existing product ecosystems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Functional Collaboration&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as primary liaison between AI engineering teams and product teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate technical capabilities into product requirements and user-centric solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help facilitate communication and alignment across engineering, product, and clinical teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive collaborative innovation processes and knowledge sharing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Infrastructure and Optimization&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Optimize cloud-based AI infrastructure for scalability, performance, and reliability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create metrics and frameworks to evaluate the effectiveness and performance of AI solutions, including autonomous agent interactions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement best practices for efficient AI system deployment and maintenance, including agentic workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Performance and Quality Assurance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and maintain rigorous testing and validation protocols for AI models&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create metrics and frameworks to evaluate the effectiveness and performance of AI solutions, including autonomous agent interactions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive continuous improvement in AI model accuracy, efficiency, and robustness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Monitoring and Observability&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement and manage monitoring solutions for AI systems to ensure operational health and performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize tools such as Langfuse, Prometheus, Grafana, or similar platforms to track model performance, latency, and resource utilization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze observability data to identify and resolve issues in AI model behavior, agentic system performance, and system reliability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish proactive monitoring strategies to detect anomalies and ensure reliability

