&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Opportunity:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Get Well is seeking a highly driven and technically strong Customer Impact Lead (Technical Program Manager) to drive end-to-end execution of customer-impacting initiatives across our healthcare platform. This role is critical in ensuring that engineering delivery translates into measurable customer outcomes by aligning product, engineering, and customer success teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate brings a strong blend of technical depth and program management expertise, with the ability to operate across complex, cross-functional environments. This role requires proactive identification of risks, dependencies, and showstoppers, while driving execution with clarity and accountability. The individual will work closely with engineering, product, customer success, and operations teams to ensure readiness for customer deployments, demos, and go-lives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition, this role will own development planning, release planning, and execution tracking across multiple workstreams to ensure predictable and high-quality delivery. Experience managing modern AI-first development lifecycles is a strong plus.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position plays a key role in improving execution efficiency and delivering high-impact outcomes in a fast-paced healthcare environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Customer Impact &amp;amp; Program Execution:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define, track, and drive customer impact milestones across key workstreams (e.g., Virtual Care, IPC, Ambulatory).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all initiatives are aligned to clear customer outcomes and timelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive end-to-end execution across multiple cross-functional programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own development planning and ensure alignment between roadmap, engineering execution, and customer priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Development &amp;amp; Release Planning:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead release planning across multiple teams, ensuring clear scope, timelines, and dependencies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track execution against plans and ensure predictable, high-quality releases.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish visibility into release readiness, risks, and go-live criteria.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Risk &amp;amp; Dependency Management:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and proactively manage critical dependencies across engineering, data, hardware, and operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Surface showstoppers early and drive mitigation plans with clear ownership and timelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure risks are clearly communicated with actionable next steps.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Functional Collaboration:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a bridge between engineering, product, and customer success teams across geographies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure alignment between what is being built and what customers need.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate closely with operations and support teams for seamless customer delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Customer-Centric Delivery:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with customer success teams to understand customer priorities and pain points.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure readiness for customer demos, deployments, and go-live activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive stabilization of high-value customer accounts through improved reliability and execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operating Rhythm &amp;amp; Reporting:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and run weekly execution and customer impact reviews.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide concise, executive-level updates on status, risks, and leadership asks.&lt;/li&gt

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Bangalore, India&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Opportunity:&lt;/strong&gt; Get Well is seeking a highly motivated Technical Product Owner to own the technical delivery of the management console and content systems—the central admin portal, the content module (CMM), media ingestion and CDN distribution, and third-party meal and medication integrations—that operational teams use to configure and scale deployments. In this role, you will be responsible for console and content technical delivery, backlog, sprint execution, and engineering coordination. You will work closely with the US Product Manager of Internal Tooling and Support while reporting into India product leadership / India PM to elevate our internal and operational tools within the healthcare technology space.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Management Console:&lt;/strong&gt; Own the full-stack lifecycle of the central admin portal and access management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Content Module (CMM):&lt;/strong&gt; Govern the core framework to upload, version, and deploy localized datasets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Media Ingestion &amp;amp; CDNs:&lt;/strong&gt; Manage ingestion pipelines, CDN distribution, and streaming for health videos.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Meal &amp;amp; Med Integrations:&lt;/strong&gt; Oversee data schemas, streams, and parsing for third-party meal ordering and drug guides.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Console Device Controls:&lt;/strong&gt; Co-own admin UI workflows for device config, room mapping, and remote restarts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Console Analytics:&lt;/strong&gt; Own tracking for admin portal sessions, bandwidth, and data sync health.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Functional Ownership:&lt;/strong&gt; Co-own shared responsibilities including offline resiliency, performance &amp;amp; latency, SDLC release alignment, payload validation, tenant onboarding, and graceful failover UX.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience:&lt;/strong&gt; 3 to 5 years as a PO / technical PO with admin, content, or platform delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education:&lt;/strong&gt; Bachelor’s degree or equivalent experience in Computer Science, Engineering, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills:&lt;/strong&gt; Full-stack admin portal or CMS experience. Familiarity with media ingestion and CDNs, and proven Agile backlog ownership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Healthcare content or localization experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with CDN, streaming, or media pipelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with third-party integrations (e.g., meal ordering, drug guides).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure to device management or admin tooling.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Get Well:&lt;/strong&gt; Now part of the SAI Group family, Get Well is redefining digital patient engagement by putting patients in control of their personalized healthcare journeys, both inside and outside the hospital. Get Well is combining high-tech AI navigation with high-touch care experiences driving patient activation, loyalty, and outcomes while reducing the cost of care. For almost 25 years, Get Well has served more than 10 million patients per year across over 1,000 hospitals and clinical partner sites, working to use longitudinal data analytics to better serve patients and clinicians. AI innovator SAI Group led by Chairman Romesh Wadhwani is the lead growth investor in Get Well. Get Well’s award-winning solutions were recognized again in 2024 by KLAS Research and AVIA Marketplace. Learn more at Get Well and follow-us on LinkedIn and Twitter.&lt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Bangalore, India&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Opportunity:&lt;/strong&gt; Get Well is seeking a highly motivated Technical Product Owner to own the technical delivery of the integration and ecosystem layer—interoperability and EHR connectivity, reusable platform APIs, IoT smart devices, multi-tenancy, and platform security—that the rest of the portfolio depends on. In this role, you will be central to executing the roadmap, owning backlog, sprint execution, and engineering coordination. You will collaborate closely with the US Product Manager of Internal Tooling and Support and report into India product leadership / India PM, ensuring that Get Well&#39;s integration infrastructure scales and excels in the health-tech environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interoperability &amp;amp; EHR:&lt;/strong&gt; Own the integration connector library, backend validation, and HL7/FHIR compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;API Library &amp;amp; Contracts:&lt;/strong&gt; Govern reusable platform APIs and secure contracts for external vendors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IoT Smart Devices:&lt;/strong&gt; Architect high-throughput IoT streams, MQTT queues, and telemetry innovations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Infrastructure Management:&lt;/strong&gt; Co-own hardware heartbeats, connection-health monitoring, and secure registration keys.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Multi-Tenancy &amp;amp; Security:&lt;/strong&gt; Enforce database isolation, OAuth/OIDC identity federation, and HIPAA security auditing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Integration Analytics:&lt;/strong&gt; Own dashboards tracking API volumes, MQTT success rates, and EMR sync latency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Functional Ownership:&lt;/strong&gt; Co-own shared responsibilities including offline resiliency, performance &amp;amp; latency, SDLC release alignment, payload validation, tenant onboarding, and graceful failover UX.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience:&lt;/strong&gt; 3 to 5 years as a PO / technical PO with integration or platform delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education:&lt;/strong&gt; Bachelor’s degree or equivalent experience in Computer Science, Engineering, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills:&lt;/strong&gt; Strong familiarity with HL7/FHIR and EHR integration. Experience with API design, governance, Agile backlog ownership, and an awareness of security and multi-tenancy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Healthcare interoperability (HL7/FHIR, Epic/Cerner) experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;IoT, MQTT, or device telemetry experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with OAuth/OIDC identity federation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure to HIPAA security auditing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
